Jesse Kriel (L) jumps to fight for the ball with Wales' centre George North (R) during an international rugby union match. AFP/Phill Magakoe BLOEMFONTEIN - Springboks coach Jacques Nienaber does not regret his decision to field a second-string side in the second Test against Wales. The world champions were stunned right at the death by the visitors who have levelled the series at 1-all before the third and final Test in Cape Town next Saturday. Nienaber made 14 changes to the starting 15 for Saturday's encounter in Bloemfontein. READ: Subs Adams, Anscombe combine to give Wales historic Springboks win Josh Adams and Gareth Anscombe combined to give Wales a series-levelling 13-12 Test win over South Africa. Wales had lost 11 previous Tests in South Africa against the Boks since 1964, including two in Bloemfontein. - Additional reporting AFP